=================================================
 GeneEats — Planner by Foodoscope
=================================================

FIRST-TIME SETUP (run once)
─────────────────────────────────────────────────
1. Create a virtual environment:
     python3 -m venv .venv          ← Mac / Linux
     python  -m venv .venv          ← Windows

2. Install dependencies:
     Mac / Linux:  .venv/bin/pip install -r backend/requirements.txt
     Windows:      .venv\Scripts\pip install -r backend\requirements.txt

3. Generate recipe data (needs the NutriDNA API server on the same network):
     Mac / Linux:  cd backend && ../.venv/bin/python3 generate_data.py && cd ..
     Windows:      cd backend && ..\\.venv\Scripts\python generate_data.py && cd ..

   NOTE: generate_data.py connects to a local API server (192.168.1.92:3030).
   Skip this step if final_output.json already exists in the backend/ folder.


RUNNING THE APP
─────────────────────────────────────────────────
  Mac / Linux:   ./start.sh
  Windows:       start.bat   (double-click it, or run in Command Prompt)

Then open your browser at:  http://localhost:8001


REFRESH DATA (browser console)
─────────────────────────────────────────────────
If the page shows stale content after re-running generate_data.py,
open DevTools (F12) → Console tab and run:

  localStorage.clear(); location.reload();


STOPPING THE APP
─────────────────────────────────────────────────
  Mac / Linux:   Press Ctrl+C in the terminal running start.sh
  Windows:       Close the Command Prompt window that ran start.bat